笔者并非理论物理的专业研究者，只是一名毕业多年、远离学术的普通爱好者。我没有前沿知识，也未受过完整训练。

促使我写下本文的，并非学识，而是十几年未曾消散的物理直觉：能量必须守恒，过程必须连续，因果必须清晰，世界必须是实在的。

本文的每一个字，都源于对这些朴素信念的忠诚。我深知其中必有疏漏，但我更相信，若远离了这些信念，物理学将迷失在数学符号的迷雾里。

若本文的思想有一丝价值，那便是它证明了：回归常识，忠于逻辑，是任何思考者——无论专业与否——都可能触摸真理的道路
物理决定数学，数学服务物理.
I am not a professional researcher in theoretical physics, but merely an ordinary enthusiast who graduated many years ago and has long been away from academic research. I possess no cutting-edge knowledge and have never received systematic academic training.
What drives me to complete this work is not specialized knowledge, but a physical intuition that has remained unchanged for more than a decade. I firmly believe that energy must be conserved, all physical processes must follow clear causality, and the world exists as objective reality.
Every viewpoint in this paper originates from these simple and fundamental beliefs. I fully recognize that there must be imperfections and omissions in my arguments. Nevertheless, I hold the conviction that once physics abandons these basic principles, it will become lost in abstract mathematical formalism.
If the ideas presented here carry any value, it is to prove that returning to common sense and adhering to rigorous logic is a valid path toward truth for every independent thinker, whether professionally trained or not.
Physics defines mathematics, and mathematics exists only to serve physics.
